  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to know that my data is granted only to the DApps I specify, so that I have control over my privacy and information. \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Currently, requests for a user's contact code or Ethereum provider come from the hosting service, typically `ipfs.infura.io/...`. \r\n\r\nOnce the user grants permission for their data, the permission is given to _any_ DApp handled by that same host.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUser grants permission on a case-by-case basis, as triggered by the DApp. \r\n\r\nAn improvement would be to grant permission for a specific DAppâ€”not for any DApp hosted by IPFS/Infura.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nMy contact code is shared with any `ipfs.infura` DApp once I grant access once.",
